01:22:14,407 --> 01:22:15,866
I got you.

1026
01:22:24,625 --> 01:22:26,001
Lord of the Plains.

1027
01:22:29,130 --> 01:22:30,339
That's me.

1029
01:23:45,664 --> 01:23:48,501
<i>Texas Highway Patrol
and the locals</i>

1030
01:23:48,667 --> 01:23:52,213
<i>chased the robbers
to this hillside behind me,</i>

1031
01:23:52,379 --> 01:23:56,425
<i>20 miles west of town,
where the gunfight continued.</i>

1032
01:23:56,592 --> 01:23:58,010
<i>And right now we do know</i>

1033
01:23:58,177 --> 01:24:02,139
<i>Ranger Marcus Hamilton
killed one of the gunmen</i>

1034
01:24:02,306 --> 01:24:05,851
<i>using a rifle he actually borrowed
from a resident here.</i>

1035
01:24:06,018 --> 01:24:09,063
<i>We don't know the name
of that suspect yet...</i>

1036
01:25:06,328 --> 01:25:07,496
Lucky guy-

1037
01:25:09,957 --> 01:25:12,209
Just in the nick of time, too.

1038
01:25:12,376 --> 01:25:13,544
What are the odds?

1039
01:25:16,839 --> 01:25:20,634
Now, this, uh, satisfies

1040
01:25:20,801 --> 01:25:23,887
both the reverse mortgage loan
and the, uh...

1041
01:25:24,054 --> 01:25:26,682
and the back taxes that we've paid
on your mother's behalf.

1042
01:25:26,849 --> 01:25:29,143
We do that as courtesy,
of course.

1043
01:25:33,522 --> 01:25:36,108
You can fax the release of lien
to that number.

1044
01:25:40,029 --> 01:25:41,155
An attorney?

1045
01:25:43,782 --> 01:25:46,452
All right, well, I'll... I'll get that
faxed over to your attorney

1046
01:25:46,619 --> 01:25:47,703
by the end of the week.

1047
01:25:47,870 --> 01:25:50,122
It is the end of the week.
I wanna watch you do it.

1048
01:25:55,002 --> 01:25:58,714
Well, it takes a little time
to prepare.

1049
01:25:58,881 --> 01:26:00,174
I got all day.

1050
01:26:08,974 --> 01:26:11,143
Here we go.

1051
01:26:11,310 --> 01:26:14,229
Okay. That's it.

1052
01:26:14,396 --> 01:26:18,192
And it's been a pleasure
doing business with you.

1053
01:26:32,998 --> 01:26:34,333
Let me ask you a question.

1054
01:26:36,126 --> 01:26:37,544
Do y'all manage trusts?

1055
01:26:43,050 --> 01:26:44,927
Hey, Marcus,
ain't you supposed to be retired?

1056
01:26:45,094 --> 01:26:46,136
Howdy.

1057
01:26:51,308 --> 01:26:53,560
- Shelley.
- Nice to see you.

1058
01:26:53,727 --> 01:26:55,604
- Well, hey, Marcus.
- Hey, Margaret.

1059
01:26:55,771 --> 01:26:57,314
Been awhile.
How's life as a civilian?

1060
01:26:57,481 --> 01:27:00,984
Oh, just, you know...

1061
01:27:01,151 --> 01:27:04,113
Think I can take a peek
at Mr. Howard's file?

1062
01:27:04,279 --> 01:27:05,447
Tanner Howard.

1063
01:27:06,949 --> 01:27:09,910
Oh, come on.
I ain't got nothing better to do.

1064
01:27:10,077 --> 01:27:11,203
It's at my desk.

1065
01:27:12,329 --> 01:27:13,455
Uh...

1066
01:27:18,669 --> 01:27:21,046
Killed his father
in a hunting accident, huh?

1067
01:27:21,213 --> 01:27:24,133
<i>I'd love to know what he was hunting
in the barn in April.</i>

1068
01:27:24,299 --> 01:27:27,761
10 years in Huntsville
for aggravated assault.

1069
01:27:27,928 --> 01:27:29,513
Cellmate was released in 2012.

1070
01:27:29,680 --> 01:27:31,056
Before that,
he served seven years

1071
01:27:31,223 --> 01:27:33,308
on bank robbery charges
up in Big Spring.

1072
01:27:33,475 --> 01:27:35,728
Been trying to track him down,
but no luck so far.

1073
01:27:35,894 --> 01:27:37,604
You all are off the brother?

1074
01:27:37,771 --> 01:27:39,690
There's nothing that links him
to the robberies.

1075
01:27:40,858 --> 01:27:43,068
Now, what about
that little waitress in Vernon?

1076
01:27:43,235 --> 01:27:44,319
Yeah, we showed her photos.

1077
01:27:44,486 --> 01:27:46,196
She said she didn't
recognize him.

1078
01:27:46,363 --> 01:27:48,657
Pretty upset you took
her tips as evidence.

1079
01:27:50,242 --> 01:27:51,827
She sure was sassy.

1080
01:27:51,994 --> 01:27:53,746
You show that
to that old timer?

1081
01:27:53,912 --> 01:27:56,623
<i>Yep. He said he didn't look
like the fella from the diner.</i>

1082
01:27:56,790 --> 01:27:59,084
He didn't recognize
Tanner's photo either.

1083
01:27:59,251 --> 01:28:02,212
Yeah, tried to get a court order
on his bank accounts and the ranch,

1084
01:28:02,379 --> 01:28:03,422
DA wouldn't do it.

1085
01:28:03,589 --> 01:28:06,091
Toby's got no record.
He's never been arrested.

1086
01:28:06,258 --> 01:28:08,385
His only court appearance
was at his divorce.

1087
01:28:08,552 --> 01:28:10,554
He don't fit the bill, Marcus.

1088
01:28:10,721 --> 01:28:12,139
People don't start out
robbing banks.

1089
01:28:12,306 --> 01:28:14,600
They graduate to it
like his asshole brother.

1090
01:28:14,767 --> 01:28:16,226
Besides,
when we was out there,

1091
01:28:16,393 --> 01:28:17,978
we saw two crews from Chevron

1092
01:28:18,145 --> 01:28:20,397
capping wells
and putting in pumpjacks.

1093
01:28:20,564 --> 01:28:22,107
Engineers out there
said they're gonna pull

1094
01:28:22,274 --> 01:28:24,485
2,000 barrels a month
off that place.

1095
01:28:24,651 --> 01:28:27,196
You just try convincing a judge
to issue warrants on somebody

1096
01:28:27,362 --> 01:28:29,031
set to clear $50,000 a month

1097
01:28:29,198 --> 01:28:32,284
for robbing $40,000 from the bank
that manages the family trust.

1098
01:28:32,451 --> 01:28:34,495
Midland manages the trust?

1099
01:28:37,831 --> 01:28:40,000
You'd think they'd want
this thing figured out.

1100
01:28:40,167 --> 01:28:42,044
I don't think the bank cares
about anything

1101
01:28:42,211 --> 01:28:43,879
but keeping that trust
right where it is.

1102
01:28:44,963 --> 01:28:47,382
Hell, they were less cooperative
than Toby's attorney.

1103
01:28:49,760 --> 01:28:53,013
Marcus, he's not a suspect
and you are retired.

1104
01:28:54,056 --> 01:28:55,224
Oh, I hear you.

1105
01:28:59,311 --> 01:29:00,687
You like my desk?

1106
01:29:02,064 --> 01:29:03,148
I don't hate it.

1107
01:29:06,068 --> 01:29:07,361
Hey, I'll see you, Marcus.

1108
01:30:44,207 --> 01:30:45,667
Know who I am?

1109
01:30:50,005 --> 01:30:52,299
I'm the man
who killed your brother.

1110
01:30:52,466 --> 01:30:53,592
I know.

1111
01:30:55,385 --> 01:30:57,721
I also know you're retired
and you're trespassing.

1112
01:30:59,014 --> 01:31:02,726
Well, you could shoot me now
and be within your rights.

1113
01:31:02,893 --> 01:31:05,896
You toting a gun and all,
how convenient.

1114
01:31:07,064 --> 01:31:08,649
I figure you got one, too.

1115
01:31:14,696 --> 01:31:15,989
Mind if I sit?

1116
01:31:20,619 --> 01:31:21,662
Go ahead.

1117
01:31:45,227 --> 01:31:46,436
You want a beer?

1118
01:31:47,646 --> 01:31:50,649
Sure.
I ain't on duty no more.

1119
01:32:01,284 --> 01:32:02,285
Thanks.

1120
01:32:07,530 --> 01:32:10,116
It's nice out here
in this breeze, huh,

1121
01:32:10,283 --> 01:32:11,910
now that it's cooled down.

1122
01:32:22,624 --> 01:32:23,750
How did you do it?

1123
01:32:26,085 --> 01:32:27,337
Oh, never mind.

1124
01:32:27,503 --> 01:32:29,422
I'll figure that out in time.

1125
01:32:29,589 --> 01:32:31,674
Why?
Why did you do it?

1126
01:32:33,509 --> 01:32:35,929
I know why your brother,
Tanner, did it.

1127
01:32:36,095 --> 01:32:38,932
He robbed them banks
because he liked it.

1128
01:32:41,389 --> 01:32:44,642
He shot my partner 300 yards away
'cause he liked it.

1129
01:32:44,809 --> 01:32:45,977
It made him feel good.

1130
01:32:48,646 --> 01:32:50,690
If I hadn't blown
his shit for brains out,

1131
01:32:50,857 --> 01:32:54,319
there'd be a new truck out front
with jet skis

1132
01:32:54,486 --> 01:32:56,362
or whatever else
he could think to buy.

1133
01:32:56,529 --> 01:33:00,742
He'd spend it all just to give
an excuse to steal some more.

1134
01:33:00,909 --> 01:33:02,285
But not you.

1135
01:33:04,863 --> 01:33:06,865
There's nothing new
around here...

1136
01:33:08,116 --> 01:33:10,994
except them pumpjacks.

1137
01:33:11,161 --> 01:33:12,746
Each one of them
making you a month

1138
01:33:12,912 --> 01:33:16,166
what you and your brother stole
from all four banks combined.

1139
01:33:17,625 --> 01:33:19,210
Help me understand, then.

1140
01:33:22,005 --> 01:33:24,257
Help me understand
why four people died...

1141
01:33:26,043 --> 01:33:29,839
so you could steal money
that it don't seem you've spent,

1142
01:33:30,006 --> 01:33:32,091
that it don't seem you need.

1143
01:33:32,258 --> 01:33:33,342
You got a family?

1144
01:33:33,509 --> 01:33:35,803
My partner had a family.
A big one.

1145
01:33:36,804 --> 01:33:38,806
They don't got no pumpjacks
in their backyard.

1146
01:33:38,973 --> 01:33:41,309
- I didn't kill your friend.
- Yes, you did.

1147
01:33:42,810 --> 01:33:44,854
By setting this thing
in motion.

1148
01:33:46,063 --> 01:33:49,233
You expect me to believe
your dimwitted brother planned this?

1149
01:33:50,443 --> 01:33:53,487
Oh, no.
This was smart.

1150
01:33:53,654 --> 01:33:54,864
This was you.

1151
01:33:58,743 --> 01:34:00,536
I've been poor my whole life.

1152
01:34:04,207 --> 01:34:06,626
So were my parents,
their parents before them.

1153
01:34:09,003 --> 01:34:10,504
It's like a disease...

1154
01:34:12,215 --> 01:34:15,176
passing from generation to generation,
becomes a sickness.

1155
01:34:15,343 --> 01:34:16,427
That's what it is.

1156
01:34:18,262 --> 01:34:19,931
Infects every person you know...

1157
01:34:21,140 --> 01:34:22,600
but not my boys.

1158
01:34:24,310 --> 01:34:25,603
Not anymore.

1159
01:34:29,357 --> 01:34:30,650
This is theirs now.

1160
01:34:35,154 --> 01:34:36,989
Now, I ain't never killed
no one in my life,

1161
01:34:37,156 --> 01:34:40,159
but if you want me to start with you,
let's get on with it, old man.

1162
01:34:41,953 --> 01:34:44,997
See if you can grab that pistol
before I blast you off this porch.

1163
01:35:24,537 --> 01:35:26,289
- Howdy.
- What's going on?

1164
01:35:27,957 --> 01:35:30,418
The hogs are back
in the garden.

1165
01:35:30,584 --> 01:35:33,045
Feral hogs tearing up this place
something fierce.

1166
01:35:34,797 --> 01:35:35,840
Who's this?

1167
01:35:36,007 --> 01:35:37,758
I'm an old friend
of your husband.

1168
01:35:38,801 --> 01:35:40,011
Ex-husband.

1169
01:35:41,971 --> 01:35:43,306
I'm just working on the house.

1170
01:35:44,432 --> 01:35:46,142
Oh, you don't live here?

1171
01:35:46,309 --> 01:35:49,103
No, it's not mine.
It's theirs.

1172
01:35:51,689 --> 01:35:53,274
Oh.

1173
01:35:53,441 --> 01:35:55,860
The things we do
for our kids, huh?

1174
01:35:58,446 --> 01:35:59,488
Well...

1175
01:36:01,532 --> 01:36:02,700
I best be going.

1176
01:36:02,867 --> 01:36:03,993
Ma'am.

1177
01:36:04,160 --> 01:36:05,953
Me, too, Debbie.
I'm gonna wash up,

1178
01:36:06,120 --> 01:36:08,748
be back around 9:00 tomorrow
to finish the front.

1179
01:36:08,914 --> 01:36:09,999
Start painting the extension

1180
01:36:10,166 --> 01:36:11,334
and then help Randy
with his homework

1181
01:36:11,500 --> 01:36:14,378
when he gets back
from school, okay?

1182
01:36:14,545 --> 01:36:15,588
Okay-

1183
01:36:18,841 --> 01:36:20,134
Hey.

1184
01:36:21,385 --> 01:36:23,304
I rent a little house in town.

1185
01:36:25,181 --> 01:36:26,932
If you wanna stop by
and finish this conversation,

1186
01:36:27,099 --> 01:36:28,309
you're welcome anytime.

1187
01:36:29,769 --> 01:36:31,270
Oh, I'd like that.

1188
01:36:32,396 --> 01:36:33,564
I'll be seeing you.

1189
01:36:33,731 --> 01:36:36,484
Yeah.
Soon, I hope.

1190
01:36:38,986 --> 01:36:40,446
I'm ready to be done
with this.

1191
01:36:40,613 --> 01:36:42,740
You'll never be done with it
no matter what.

1192
01:36:42,907 --> 01:36:45,451
It's gonna haunt you, son,
for the rest of your days.

1193
01:36:46,494 --> 01:36:48,245
But you won't be alone.

1194
01:36:48,412 --> 01:36:49,955
It's gonna haunt me, too.

1195
01:36:50,122 --> 01:36:52,208
If you stop by,
maybe I'll give you peace.

1196
01:36:52,375 --> 01:36:56,253
Maybe.
Maybe I'll give it to you.

